            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 7.6-cm x 7.6-cm cylindrical 'plug' detector",
                " surrounded by an axially split NaI(Tl) annulus in",
                " anticoincidence mode used to detect gammas."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector consisted of a 1-mm-thick silicon",
                " detector which was fixed at an angle 135. degr.",
                " relative to the forward beam direction and was",
                " protected from the back-angle elastically deuterons",
                " by a 2-mg/cm2 aluminum foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
